full_text: Form approved. Budget Bureau No. 43-R344.1 UNITED STATES DEPARTMENT OF JUSTICE IMMIGRATION AND NATURALIZATION SERVICE APPLICATION FOR TRANSFER OF PETITION FOR NATURALIZATION (Under Section 335 (i), Immigration and Nationality Act) No. 482-P-27899 To the Honorable, the U.S. District Court of Southern District of Florida at Miami, Florida I, Florence Cohen , now residing at 417 N. 32nd Place, Apt. 5 (Name of applicant) (Street and number) Phoenix Arizona (City) (County) , (State) having filed petition for naturalization No. 27899 in this Court on Oct. 15, 1962 (Month) (Day) , and having removed (Year) from the jurisdiction of said Court on Oct. 25, 1962 (Month) 9 (Day) hereby make application (Year) for the transfer of my petition to the U.S. District Court at Phoenix, Arizona (City and State) , in accordance with the provisions of section 335 (i) of the Immigration and Nationality Act. Cohen (Signature of applicant) Subscribed and sworn to before me by the above named petitioner at Phoenix, Arizona (City and State) this 13th day of November, 19 62 MURRAY ISRAEL, [SEAL] GENERAL ATTORNEY, NATIONALITY. (Title) To APPLICANT: You must execute this application in quadruplicate, sign and be sworn to it. The application be executed before an officer of the Immigration and Naturalization Service without the payment of may it fee for such execution. If not executed before an officer of the Immigration and Naturalization Service, any must be executed before a notary public, clerk of court, or other officer authorized to administer oaths for general purposes, and the seal of the notary, clerk, or other officer must be impressed where indicated. your petition. Submit the application to the office of the Immigration and Naturalization Service through which you filed Form N-455 (Rev. 8-20-58)
